      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_a8cfce17114baf988a3345551d93af0b">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Yale Women's Action Committee Records (RU 477). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_0a891b7b7b427f0bcf0a99855d952651">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ee93e3726fdfd849b675263fe0a03db1">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of clippings, reports, and correspondence documenting the Yale Women's Action Committee study of sexual and gender harassment at Yale. Also includes a report and newsclipping concerning sexual harassment at Harvard.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_59a538cc0097df488d5c17f13cb92635">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
